# Site currency formats

BattleDrop reads display currency from `public.site_settings.default_currency` (singleton row). Admins edit it at `/admin-panel/settings`. Signed-in users can override currency display at `/settings`.

## Priority

For `currency`:

1. **User preference** — `public.users.currency` (nullable)
2. **Site default** — `public.site_settings.default_currency` when the user value is `null`
3. **Hardcoded fallback** — `DEFAULT_SITE_SETTINGS.defaultCurrency` in `app/lib/site-settings-types.ts`

Merge with `resolveEffectiveCurrency()` in `app/lib/site-settings/resolve-effective-currency-settings.ts`.

For the signed-in viewer, prefer `getEffectiveCurrencyForUser(userId)` in `app/lib/users/user-currency-preferences.ts`. Guests use site settings only.

## Source of truth

| Layer | What |
|-------|------|
| DB site | `default_currency` on `public.site_settings` |
| DB user | `currency` (nullable) on `public.users` |
| Server read site | `getSiteSettings()` in `app/lib/site-settings/get-site-settings.ts` |
| Server read user | `getUserCurrencyPreference()` / `currency` on `getCurrentAppUser()` |
| Types & low-level formatters | `app/lib/site-settings-types.ts` |
| App helpers | `app/lib/site-settings/format-display-money.ts` |
| User API | `PATCH /api/user-settings` (auth required; includes `currency`) |
| Admin API | `PATCH /api/site-settings` (admin only; includes `defaultCurrency`) |

## Never hardcode currency symbols

```typescript
// BAD — bypasses site/user settings
`€${amount}`
"$5.00"
```

## Always use site formatters

```typescript
// Server components / route handlers
import { getEffectiveCurrencyForUser } from "@/app/lib/users/user-currency-preferences";
import { formatDisplayMoney, formatDisplayMoneyWithPoints } from "@/app/lib/site-settings/format-display-money";

const currency = await getEffectiveCurrencyForUser(userId);
formatDisplayMoney(submitPrice, currency);
formatDisplayMoneyWithPoints(submitPrice, currency);
```

```typescript
// Client components — read from context (root layout merges user + site)
import { useSiteCurrency } from "@/app/components/site-currency-settings-provider";
import { formatDisplayMoneyWithPoints } from "@/app/lib/site-settings/format-display-money";

const currency = useSiteCurrency();
formatDisplayMoneyWithPoints(5, currency);
```

Root layout passes **effective** currency (user override applied) into `SiteCurrencySettingsProvider`.

## Function guide

| Function | Use when |
|----------|----------|
| `resolveEffectiveCurrency(siteDefault, userPrefs?)` | Merge user + site currency |
| `getEffectiveCurrencyForUser(userId)` | Server: resolved currency for one viewer |
| `formatDisplayMoney(amount, currency?)` | Format a numeric amount with symbol |
| `formatDisplayMoneyWithPoints(amount, currency?)` | Entry fee style: `"€5.00 or 5 points"` |
| `getCurrencySymbol(currency)` | Symbol only (admin inputs, labels) |
| `formatSiteMoney(amount, currency)` | Low-level formatter in `site-settings-types.ts` |

Optional `currency` falls back to `DEFAULT_SITE_SETTINGS.defaultCurrency`.

## After changing currency

- Admin: `PATCH /api/site-settings` calls `revalidateTag("site-settings")`.
- User: `PATCH /api/user-settings` then `router.refresh()` on the settings form so layout reloads provider values.

## Settings pages

| Route | Who | Editable |
|-------|-----|----------|
| `/admin-panel/settings` | Admin | Site default currency (`defaultCurrency`) |
| `/settings` | Signed-in user | Personal currency override (`currency`; null = site default) |

## Amounts vs currency

- `battle_submit_price` and `battle_week_settings.submit_price` store numeric amounts only.
- Currency is display-only; amounts are interpreted in the site billing currency.
- Admin battle-week UI uses **site** default currency, not the admin's personal override.
